### Dart ###
# See https://www.dartlang.org/guides/libraries/private-files
# When building your application, it is recommended to check in pubspec.lock.
#pubspec.lock
# For library packages, do not commit the pubspec.lock file.
# Regenerating the pubspec.lock file allows testing packages against the latest compatible versions of dependencies.
# See https://dart.dev/guides/libraries/private-files#pubspeclock

# Dart documentation generated by the dart doc command
# You can remove this line if you do not generate documentation locally.
# Not commonly used in applications; check in during package development
doc/api/
**/doc/api/

# Files and directories generated by pub
.dart_tool/

# dotenv environment variable files
.env*
!.env.example

# Do not commit generated JavaScript files:
*.dart.js
*.info.json      # Produced by the --dump-info flag.
*.js             # When generated by dart2js. Don't specify *.js if your
                 # project includes source files written in JavaScript.
*.js_
*.js.deps
*.js.map

